<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="510" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1254,1494]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1291,1315]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Remarks.</emphasis>
The identity of this species is uncertain. It was described by Matsumura from only female specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[338,423,1326,1350]" name="Taiwan" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, based only on external characters. Knight (
<number box="[921,979,1326,1350]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" value="1987.0">1987</number>
) mentioned the species as unknown and included it in his checklist of world species without description, and Webb &amp; Vilbaste (
<number box="[1129,1187,1362,1386]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" value="1994.0">1994</number>
) placed it as a species 
<emphasis box="[151,306,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">incertae sedis</emphasis>
for lack of description of the male genitalia. Although Dai 
<emphasis box="[973,1022,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1044,1103,1398,1422]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) compared 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1379,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botelensis">
<emphasis box="[1236,1379,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">B. botelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,315,1435,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridinervis">
<emphasis box="[151,315,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">B. viridinervis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on aedeagal characters, in their key to species they gave no details on the material they examined.
</paragraph>
